    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1950-11-22T17:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1950-11-22T17:00:00-05:00" n="113"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d113">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">460.509/11–2150: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Embassy in France</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d113fn1">This telegram, which was repeated to London as
                        2687, had the concurrence of the Department of Commerce, the Department of
                        Defense, and the Economic Cooperation Administration.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                        <lb/>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">priority</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1950-11-22T17:00:00-05:00"
                            >November 22, 1950—5 p. m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>2823. <gloss target="#t_Excon1">Excon</gloss>
                    <gloss target="#t_USDel1">USDel</gloss>. Be London’s 2959 Nov 21 rptd Paris
                        957<note n="2" xml:id="d113fn2">
                        <hi rend="italic">Supra</hi>.</note> and previous messages in this
                    series.</p>
                <list>
                    <label>1.</label>
                    <item>Agreement reached in London tripartite talks, as reflected in agreed
                        report to <gloss target="#t_FonMin1">FonMin</gloss>s (Doc TRI/31 and
                            annexes<note n="3" xml:id="d113fn3">November 20, <ref target="#pg_234"
                                >p. 234</ref>.</note>), represents very substantial progress in
                        field of internatl security export controls and is accepted by US Govt.<note
                            n="4" xml:id="d113fn4">Notification of American acceptance of the Agreed
                            Report was conveyed to the French Foreign Ministry on November 24.
                            Formal British and French approval followed shortly thereafter.</note>
                    </item>
                    <label>2.</label>
                    <item>All interested agencies most gratified with results obtained. Dept pleased
                        to commend all members of del, under chairmanship Bohlen, for their
                        excellent teamwork and individual contributions in carrying this lengthy and
                        complicated negots to successful conclusion.</item>
                    <label>3.</label>
                    <item>Assume that <gloss target="#t_Emb1">Emb</gloss>s London and Paris have
                        expressed to <gloss target="#t_FonOff1">FonOff</gloss> in most appropriate
                        manner Depts recognition their econ and polit difficulties in approaching
                        this problem and appreciation their spirit of accommodation as shown in
                        final results. Pls express also to Brit appreciation burden placed on them
                        as host govt and most efficient handling these mtgs.</item>
                    <pb facs="0260" n="244" xml:id="pg_244"/>
                    <label>4.</label>
                    <item>Dept is considering what shld be said to other dels <gloss target="#t_CG1"
                            >CG</gloss> concerning US attitude toward further changes in internatl
                        lists and concerning US export policy in light of <gloss target="#t_NSC1"
                            >NSC</gloss> meeting scheduled today.</item>
                </list>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Acheson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
